# Cursor Agent Rules — MM26 NCAAM
# Claude.ai is the strategic thought partner. Cursor is the execution agent.
# GitHub (DECISIONS.md) is the source of truth.

## Role & Mindset
You are the execution agent for this project. Translate decisions from DECISIONS.md 
into working, tested code. Flag major architectural or modeling decisions to the human 
for Claude.ai discussion — do not decide those alone.

## Before Writing Any Code
1. Read DECISIONS.md first. If a decision is marked Open, flag it before implementing.
2. Check the experiment log in DECISIONS.md. Don't repeat failed approaches.
3. Confirm the current phase before building ahead.

## Code Standards
- Python 3.10+, type hints on all functions, docstrings required
- All file paths via pathlib.Path, no hardcoded strings
- data/raw/ is READ ONLY — never write to it
- Log row counts at each transformation step
- Never train on test-year data (leave-one-tournament-out CV)
- Save models to outputs/models/ with timein filename
- Run pytest before committing

## After Changes
Append a row to the Experiment Log in DECISIONS.md: date, task, result, next step.

## What to Flag to Human (for Claude.ai)
- Model architecture or algorithm choices
- Feature engineering strategy changes
- Surprisingly good results (may indicate data leakage)
- Any ambiguity in DECISIONS.md

## Git Discipline
- Commit after every completed working task
- Format: [type]: description (types: feat, fix, data, model, test, docs)
- Never commit broken code to main
- Always commit DECISIONS.md updates alongside code changes
